<TITLE> S.Africa makes arrest in Oprah school abuse case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 JOHANNESBURG, Nov 2 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - South African police said on Friday they had arrested a former dormitory employee at Oprah Winfrey's leadership academy for girls on charges of abuse, including indecent acts. "A former dormitory employee (27) has been arrested yesterday by the Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit on several charges of abuse," a statement from police spokesman Superintendent Lungelo Dlamini read.
